node.text:
The biggest animal on Earth via @adam_ernster. 🐋 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on explorationfervor.com (link in my bio: @explorationfervor)

Blue Whales can hold their breath for about 90 minutes, reaching a maximum length of 100 feet or 30 metres long and weight up to 200 tons, it is the largest animal known to have ever existed... 🤯

This video was taken in the Santa Barbara Channel where over 27 different types of whales and dolphins call this place home, making these waters one of the best whale watching areas in the world.

From May to September you can see Blue Whales, Minke Whales and Humpback Whales. Occasionally, you can see Right Whales or Orcas. All season long you have an excellent chance of seeing dolphins, porpoises, seals and sea lions.

Who would you share this experience with? 🐳

📽 @condorexpresssb & @adam_ernster
📍 Santa Barbara, California, USA
🎶 Thomas Newman - Wow

node.text:
Ronda in Spain 🇪🇸 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @explorationfervor

Located in southern Spain is split in two by the narrow El Tajo Gorge with the old town on the southern side of the chasm and the new town on the northern side. The Guadalevín River flows through the 120m (394ft) deep gorge and out in the valley to the west of Ronda. There are three bridges connecting the old town with the new: Puente Viejo (Old Bridge), Puente Romano and Puente Nuevo (New Bridge).

Puente Nuevo is the biggest and the most impressing of the bridges. The bridge alone is reason enough to visit Ronda if you have the slightest interest in architecture. The first attempt to build a bridge at this spot started in 1735 using a single arch design. It was an ill-fated project ending in 1741 when the entire bridge collapsed causing the death of 50 workers.

The second attempt at constructing the new bridge was carefully planned and executed. It required 34 years (1759 - 1793) to complete Puente Nuevo, and the result is astonishing. The 98m high bridge is a stunning piece of architecture.
There is a room above the central arch that has been used for various purposes during the years. It has been a prison, bar and now houses a museum dedicated to the history of the bridge. 📸

1, 5. @jude_newkirk
2. @world_walkerz
3, 4. @jamesrelfdyer

Postcards from Turkey 🍃 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @explorationfervor

Have you ever been to this beautiful country before?

Turkey has 44 National Parks that look after its stunning natural heritage – so if you decide to visit, you’ll have plenty of options to choose from (some of our favorites are the Yedigoller National Park and the Saklikent Milli Park). 🌳🇹🇷 Tag a @nature lover!

📷 @cumacevikphoto
📍Turkey

node.text:
Bioluminescent algae at Jervis Bay, NSW 🇦🇺 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @explorationfervor

They are a group of tiny marine organisms that can produce an ethereal glow in the dark. The algae's glow is actually a natural defense mechanism; the light flashes occur when the algae's environment is disturbed.

When the mass of dinoflagellates are mixed up by waves or larger ocean life, a chemical reaction involving enzyme luciferase and compound luciferin produced by the algae is what causes bioluminescence, the creation of light by a living organism.

📷 @Jordan_Robins
